com.xilinx.rapidwright.design

Class TileRectangle

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.design.TileRectangle
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    RelocatableTileRectangle, SimpleTileRectangle

    public abstract class TileRectangle
extends Object
    A Rectangle of tiles, i.e. a Bounding Box around some Set of Tiles. The tiles at the edge of the rectangle (e.g. at minX/minY and maxX/maxY) are all assumed to be inside the rectangle. For both X and Y: min <= Tiles <= max The way to store tiles is set by subclasses. Depending on the storage method, they may or may not be relocatable

      • extendToCorresponding

        public abstract void extendToCorresponding(RelocatableTileRectangle rect,
                                           Site currentAnchor,
                                           SiteInst templateAnchor)
        Extend the Rectangle so that a shifted rectangle is inside. The Rectangle is assumed to be located relative to some anchor. The anchor is shifted from templateAnchor to currentAnchor. This location relative to the new anchor is then included in the Rectangle.
        Parameters:
        rect - Rectangle to include after shifting
        currentAnchor - target anchor
        templateAnchor - source anchor
